<!-- nuget.config (repo root) — hermetic: local restores must resolve EXACTLY what CI does, and
     nothing else. This repo depends only on public packages; the FS.GG.Audio.* packages are
     ProjectReferences, not deps.

     `<clear />` alone could NOT keep that promise (#31). It clears <packageSources>, and the F# SDK
     does not add its bundled FSharp.Core there — it appends `<sdk>/FSharp/library-packs` to the
     MSBuild property RestoreAdditionalProjectSources, which NuGet honours and `<clear />` never sees.
     That bundled copy is a different build of FSharp.Core from nuget.org's, with a different lock
     contentHash, so whichever source won wrote ITS hash into packages.lock.json — a machine-dependent
     lock file, and NU1403 for everyone who resolved the other way.

     packageSourceMapping is the fix, because it is the only mechanism that constrains the sources
     NuGet is HANDED rather than the sources this file DECLARES: a package may be restored only from a
     source named in the mapping, so an implicitly appended feed is refused no matter who appended it.
     NuGet says so out loud — "PackageSourceMapping is enabled, the following source(s) were not
     considered: .../library-packs".

     The mapping needs its own <clear />: an inherited machine-level mapping would otherwise merge in,
     which is the same shadowing bug one level up. It is also why this bug reproduces on a clean CI
     runner but NOT on a dev box that happens to have a machine-level mapping already excluding
     library-packs — the two boxes were never running the same restore.

     Directory.Build.props additionally sets DisableImplicitLibraryPacksFolder, the SDK's own switch,
     so the source is never appended in the first place. Either alone suffices; both together mean
     this cannot regress if one is removed, or if the SDK renames its switch. -->
<configuration>
  <packageSources>
    <clear />
    <add key="nuget.org" value="https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json" />
  </packageSources>
  <packageSourceMapping>
    <clear />
    <packageSource key="nuget.org">
      <package pattern="*" />
    </packageSource>
  </packageSourceMapping>
</configuration>
